Jenna Etheridge, News24SA Military Police vehicle. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A medical orderly stationed at a military unit in Lyttelton, Centurion, allegedly sexually harassed a patient in the sickbay, the SA National Defence Force said on Monday.The captain, who worked at the 68 Air School sick bay for the SA Military Health Service, was arrested on Sunday, said Colonel Ronald Maseko.He was transferred from the military aviation training unit to the area military health unit in Gezina so the investigation could proceed without interference or influence."Whilst the investigations were ongoing, he allegedly tried to bribe the investigating officer to have his case not prosecuted in court."Maseko said the arrest was a result of co-operation between the Military Police and the SA Police Service.The captain&nbsp;was expected to appear in court later on Monday."The SANDF condemns any form or type of ill-discipline within its ranks, regardless of member&rsquo;s appointment and/or position," said Maseko.WATCH this video:24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.